                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="419513" author="JIRAUSER18433" created="Mon, 1 Jul 2024 18:30:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is mostly aimed at QEMU and other local virtual testing environments. If the network gets setup incorrectly, LNet will complain. The traffic will pass over lo0 anyway. So I think it&apos;s best to sidestep the issue by avoiding setting up ksocklnd altogether.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="419437" author="bzzz" created="Mon, 1 Jul 2024 04:39:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;but you need to access that machine somehow so you already have a running nic ?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="419430" author="gerrit" created="Mon, 1 Jul 2024 02:14:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&quot;Timothy Day &amp;lt;timday@amazon.com&amp;gt;&quot; uploaded a new patch: &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/55587&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/55587&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
